To evaluate $P(|Y / n-0.25|<0.05)$, we can use Chebyshev's inequality, which states that for any random variable $X$ with mean $\mu$ and variance $\sigma^2$, $P(|X - \mu| \geq k) \leq \frac{\sigma^2}{k^2}$. The complementary probability is $P(|X - \mu| < k) \geq 1 - \frac{\sigma^2}{k^2}$.

