## Step 2
Let's consider the probability of a match on the $i$th draw, denoted as event $A_i$. The probability of $A_i$ happening is the probability that the $i$th ball drawn is the one numbered $i$. Initially, there are $n$ balls, so the probability of drawing the ball numbered $i$ on the $i$th draw involves considering the total number of ways the draws can happen before the $i$th draw.

